 {"id":"br-r37-c1-02","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] node_connectivity on MultiGraph with parallel edges returned simple-graph value","description":"fnx.node_connectivity(MultiGraph) called into _raw_node_connectivity which collapses parallel edges. On e.g. K3 with extra parallel edges between two pairs, networkx returns min-degree=3 (parallel edges inflate the degree bound) while fnx returned 2 (simple-graph κ=n−1). Fixed by delegating multigraph inputs to networkx to preserve parity. Simple Graph/DiGraph continue to use the Rust fast path.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: node_connectivity now delegates when G.is_multigraph(). Verified on K3-parallel, K3 MG no-parallel, MDG with parallel edges — all match nx.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-03","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] edge_connectivity returned float and ignored MultiGraph parallel edges","description":"Two related defects in edge_connectivity: (1) simple Graph path returned a float (e.g. 2.0) via the max-flow pipeline while nx returns an int cardinality (2). (2) MultiGraph path collapsed parallel edges: on K3 with extra parallel edges fnx returned 2.0 vs nx's 3. Fixed by coercing int-valued floats to int before returning, and delegating multigraph inputs to networkx.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: MG/MDG delegate to nx; simple Graph path casts integral float back to int. Verified across K3 simple, DG, MG with/without parallel, MDG — all match nx in value and type.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-19x8x","title":"parity: ISMAGS class missing from isomorphism API","description":"NetworkX exposes networkx.algorithms.isomorphism.ISMAGS(graph, subgraph, node_match=None, edge_match=None, cache=None) with is_isomorphic(), isomorphisms_iter(), subgraph_is_isomorphic(), subgraph_isomorphisms_iter(), and largest_common_subgraph(). FrankenNetworkX does not export ISMAGS. Add an ISMAGS wrapper that converts FrankenNetworkX graph objects via _networkx_graph_for_parity and delegates to NetworkX, plus parity tests for constructor signature and core methods.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:25:45.112099160Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:30:32.434165705Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:30:32.432309961Z","close_reason":"Completed in 2c0f4aa","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-5nop9","title":"parity: bfs_labeled_edges public signature should be (G, sources) matching networkx","description":"fnx.bfs_labeled_edges has signature (G, sources=None, sort_neighbors=None, *, source=None) — three problems vs nx (G, sources): sources is required in nx but optional here, sort_neighbors is not part of upstream signature, source is a keyword-only legacy alias. Even though both shapes appear to function, the public signature divergence is observable via inspect.signature, breaks parameter introspection used by typed wrappers, and means typer-style strict argument routing breaks. Tighten the wrapper to (G, sources) matching nx; if downstream callers pass sort_neighbors/source those are unsupported by nx and should fail loudly.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T01:09:39.386409859Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T01:14:39.290123125Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-5q77h","title":"parity: bipartite matching/cluster/basic/redundancy wrappers missing (12 functions)","description":"networkx.algorithms.bipartite exposes 12 functions not surfaced by franken_networkx: matching family (eppstein_matching, maximum_matching, minimum_weight_full_matching, to_vertex_cover), cluster family (cc_dot, cc_max, cc_min, latapy_clustering, robins_alexander_clustering), basic (degrees, sets), and redundancy (node_redundancy). Add Python wrappers in __init__.py via a new _call_networkx_bipartite_for_parity helper, export at top-level, add to __all__ under bipartite section.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:04:07.582914231Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:21:47.577934437Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:21:47.575865893Z","close_reason":"Shipped in f6a631a: 12 bipartite wrappers via _call_networkx_bipartite_for_parity helper (cc_dot/cc_max/cc_min routed through nx.algorithms.bipartite.cluster). All verified against nx on K33 + weighted 3x3 bipartite graph.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"br-r37-c1-71glx","title":"parity: 3 signature mismatches (gaussian_random_partition_graph arg order, find_minimal_d_separator wrong sig, to_nested_tuple leaks _parent)","description":"Three signature-parity defects discovered while signature-diffing fnx __all__ vs upstream nx (excluding backend dispatch noise). (1) gaussian_random_partition_graph: nx is (n, s, v, p_in, p_out, directed=False, seed=None) but fnx is (n, s, v, p_in, p_out, seed=None, directed=False) — positional arg order swapped, breaks calls like nx.gaussian_random_partition_graph(10, 5, 0.1, 0.4, 0.05, True). (2) find_minimal_d_separator: nx is (G, x, y, *, included=None, restricted=None) but fnx is (G, u, v) — wrong param names AND missing keyword-only included/restricted. (3) to_nested_tuple: fnx leaks an internal _parent=None recursion arg in its public signature. Fix: align signatures; for find_minimal_d_separator, route through nx via _call_networkx_for_parity to handle the new kwargs.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T00:49:37.606667646Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T00:54:39.238733080Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-71glx","title":"parity: 3 signature mismatches (gaussian_random_partition_graph arg order, find_minimal_d_separator wrong sig, to_nested_tuple leaks _parent)","description":"Three signature-parity defects discovered while signature-diffing fnx __all__ vs upstream nx (excluding backend dispatch noise). (1) gaussian_random_partition_graph: nx is (n, s, v, p_in, p_out, directed=False, seed=None) but fnx is (n, s, v, p_in, p_out, seed=None, directed=False) — positional arg order swapped, breaks calls like nx.gaussian_random_partition_graph(10, 5, 0.1, 0.4, 0.05, True). (2) find_minimal_d_separator: nx is (G, x, y, *, included=None, restricted=None) but fnx is (G, u, v) — wrong param names AND missing keyword-only included/restricted. (3) to_nested_tuple: fnx leaks an internal _parent=None recursion arg in its public signature. Fix: align signatures; for find_minimal_d_separator, route through nx via _call_networkx_for_parity to handle the new kwargs.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T00:49:37.606667646Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T01:04:38.730801947Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T01:04:38.728883324Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 21b0340: 3 signature fixes (gaussian_random_partition_graph arg order, find_minimal_d_separator delegated to nx with included/restricted kwargs, to_nested_tuple no longer leaks _parent). Smoke test still passes 170/170.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-75r94","title":"parity: coloring strategy_* (8) + matching_dict_to_set (1) wrappers","description":"Two clusters of nx utilities not surfaced. Coloring strategies (used as strategy= argument to greedy_color): strategy_largest_first(G, colors), strategy_random_sequential(G, colors, seed=None), strategy_smallest_last(G, colors), strategy_independent_set(G, colors), strategy_connected_sequential_bfs(G, colors), strategy_connected_sequential_dfs(G, colors), strategy_connected_sequential(G, colors, traversal=bfs), strategy_saturation_largest_first(G, colors). Matching utility: matching_dict_to_set(matching) — converts a {node: partner} dict to a set of (u, v) frozensets. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level + __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T23:29:37.916763877Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T23:44:39.656055329Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T23:44:39.653993535Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 7939284: 8 strategy_* coloring callables + matching_dict_to_set. Verified with nx.greedy_color(C6, strategy=fnx.strategy_largest_first) matching nx output. Follow-up: fnx.greedy_color does not accept callable strategies (only strings) — separate parity gap.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-7u6up","title":"parity: community edge_betweenness_partition + greedy_source_expansion missing","description":"Two community-detection helpers from networkx.algorithms.community not exposed by franken_networkx: edge_betweenness_partition(G, number_of_sets, weight=None) and greedy_source_expansion(G, source, ...). Add Python wrappers delegating via _call_networkx_community_for_parity, export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T12:13:47.981273951Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:50.852667948Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:50.850778351Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 4eb0d6d: edge_betweenness_partition + greedy_source_expansion verified on karate","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-8vobd","title":"parity: approximation TSP family wrappers missing (christofides, greedy_tsp, simulated_annealing/threshold_accepting_tsp, traveling_salesman_problem, asadpour_atsp, metric_closure)","description":"networkx.algorithms.approximation exposes a TSP/metric family that franken_networkx does not: traveling_salesman_problem, christofides, greedy_tsp, simulated_annealing_tsp, threshold_accepting_tsp, asadpour_atsp, metric_closure. All are pure approximation algorithms with no parity-sensitive Rust counterpart in fnx. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py delegating to nx.algorithms.approximation via a new _call_networkx_approximation_for_parity helper (mirrors community/connectivity helpers). Export at top-level and add to __all__. Verify each on a small graph (cycle_graph(5) for TSP, complete_graph(4) for metric_closure).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T17:28:04.863008794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T17:56:54.641577638Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T17:56:54.638612839Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 07416f9: 7 TSP/metric wrappers via _call_networkx_approximation_for_parity helper. Verified greedy_tsp/christofides/traveling_salesman_problem match nx exactly on K4; asadpour_atsp valid on 3-node digraph; sa/ta_tsp produce valid cycles.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
